BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 9 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and China 
signed a memorandum in Beijing Saturday on agricultural 
information exchange, cross-visits of experts and other 
cooperation measures. 
  Kim Kwang-hui, head of the rural development administration, 
signed the memorandum of understanding with Wang Lianzheng, 
president of the Academy of Agricultural Sciences in China, as 
one of the follow-up measures to the agreement at last 
November's Science-technology Cooperation Committee meeting, 
officials here said. 
  Seoul and Beijing will establish systematic ways of 
exchanging farming technology as well as latest information on 
rural science. Officials said they especially hope for access to 
wide range of China's rich variant agricultural products. 

